orthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Keeping aggro at lvl40</span><hr size=1> I'm having trouble keeping aggro at lvl40 from monks and other tanks.  Sure, hitting taunt brings it back, but I always seem to lose it again.  As I'm 2boxing with my cleric, it gets annoying to have to split heals and the monks get totally beat up following their recent nerf.<br>
<br>
Right now, I'm using Defiance+LSOEE and SCHW (the rest of my gear is linked below.)  I thought that would do it, but so far my experience is that I keep losing it.  Strangely, I seemed to have more luck with Wurmy+LSOEE but that flies in the face of conventional wisdom, so I'm reluctant to believe it (and I used it only to a limited extent so my data points are few.)<br>
<br>
Any suggestions on what do I need to do?  I could upgrade the defiance to a frosty or a snowchipper, but I hate relying on procs for aggro (and with an unbuffed dex of less than 100 I can't see that working well anyway.)  I only have about 10k to spend, but I certainly am interested in any camps or questing I can do (remember I'm level 40 though.)<br>
<br>
A buddy just picked up a crecent blade of luclin for his mainhand - is that an aggro-holdling replacement for  defiance I should consider (I have no 1hp skill now but that's pretty easily corrected.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=464143" target="top">Zeds Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - yet another character who wishes he wasn't agnostic. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scottsh>scottsh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boardpics.bravepages.com/smiley.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/9/03 11:14:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorilan>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 12:19:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Keeping aggro at lvl40</span><hr size=1> get a frostbringer since you are 40 if you can. they arnt to expencive .<br>
<br>
and the next thing on your list will probly be an RBG. i see them for about 16-20k (been a month or 2 since i last looked though so dont quote me)<br>
<br>
from your gear i see that it might be a while though before you have some money for the higher stuff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shikariiapoccalypse>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All in the reflexes</BR>Guardian of the Bunker</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 2252<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 11:22:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Keeping aggro at lvl40</span><hr size=1> actually zeds the wurmy is about at the end of it's life in regards to DPS and speed/bonus dmg, but for you in your late 30's-early 40's the Wurmy was doing the most in terms of DPS/Aggro. I think it was about at level 44 or so the faster 1H's + their damage bonuses made them better choices than the wurmy.<br>
<br>
On what to upgrade, that path is split and can be looked at in 2 different ways:<br>
<br>
1. cheapest aggro weapons you'd come across is a Black Blade of Tormenting and a Praetor's Blade of Debility. Hell, I used them at level 60 against Vindi and did well if you need a benchmark ( their upgrade was my epics btw ). DPS wise a 9/22 sucks, but the proc was killer.<br>
2. most common and longevity-minded aggro weapon is the Frostbringer. It's like Aggro_101, plus it's nice ratio makes it valid for many uses and levels.<br>
<br>
In time you'll come to rely a bit more on procs; but I know where you're coming from. I was a firm believer in DPS&gt;proc, but over the course of many weapons and many many days it became evident that even with a % chance to proc, it was wellw orth the investment. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/crushr85/myhomepage/max.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scottsh>scottsh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boardpics.bravepages.com/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 6:43:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Keeping aggro at lvl40</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice, it is really appreciated.<br>
