Zeds <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 368<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 10:04:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   your aggro problems in a nutshell</span><hr size=1> Here's why you're having a problem holding aggro:<br>
<br>
1) Monk skillcaps are higher than yours at level 40, so your monk friend is going to have a higher ATK and with comprable weapons will put out more DPS than you.<br>
<br>
2) Your monk friend, I'm betting has something along the lines of a Jade Mace or Goranga Spiked Club or some huge honking 2hb? If so, your 9/19 mainhand isn't going to produce enough DPS to drag the mob off of the spam machine known as monk.<br>
<br>
3) You're monk friend isn't evading, by fiegning death when he gets aggro and waiting for you to build up some aggro?<br>
<br>
My advice ...<br>
<br>
Let the monk tank.<br>
<br>
You're only level 40. You don't NEED to hold aggro. If your monk friend has any monk gear that's worth a damn, odds are he's got as much or more AC than you and his HPs aren't lagging THAT far behind.<br>
<br>
The monk nerf is a non-issue for what you're fighting. Your monk friend can tank just as well as ever on melee crap at level 40.<br>
<br>
Worry about holding aggro when you finally start to do raid type stuff. In XP groups, don't sweat the small stuff.<br>
<br>
-Wubao <br>
59 monk of Povar<br>
Fist of Agnost the Indifferent <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scottsh>scottsh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boardpics.bravepages.com/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/12/03 12:57:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: your aggro problems in a nutshell</span><hr size=1> Interesting response, and I appreciate where you are coming from.  It's just annoying to have to split heals as the cleric in the group too (I'm 2boxing the war+clr.)  It also hurts the monk to be getting doged, parried, and reposted - lowering his overall DPS.<br>
<br>
It is more mana efficient if I can Complete Heal the warrior (who has more HP, about 2500 buffed at 40) for 1500 than split the 600 point heals between the monk and warrior.  Thus, I'd like to hold the aggro even if it means lowering the DPS - the overall group efficiency will be better.<br>
<br>
I'm going to try using my Kunzar Katach mainhand (with LSOEE offhand) to try to keep the aggro with the proc.  If I have good luck with that, I may upgrade to the Frostbringer. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scottsh>scottsh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boardpics.bravepages.com/smiley.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/12/03 11:55:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 291<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/12/03 2:15:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: your aggro problems in a nutshell</span><hr size=1> Sell the LSoEE.  Just do yourself a favor and get rid of it.  Take the money you make and upgrade weapons, haste and armor if you can.  Its tough going when you are prePoH/Kael, but if you just can't hold agro for poo, let the monk do it.  As you level and are able to aquire items from PoH/Kael, then you'll see your dex get better and procing weapons will be more useful.<br>
<br>
Good luck =) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124485">Deterious</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 369<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/12/03 5:58:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   nod</span><hr size=1> Aye, keeping aggro on one person the duration of the fight would help your mana pool.<br>
<br>
So, uh, what's your monk friend doing to help with this?<br>
<br>
When he gets aggro, does he immediately feign it off back onto you?<br>
<br>
Has he considered staying further away from the mob while you move right up on its toes?<br>
<br>
Has he considered using a slightly lower DPS combo? Or even just a 2hand weapon, which at those levels will be less DPS because of the lack of high damage bonus?<br>
<br>
IF ALL of these ideas are failing or not working, then you have one SURE FIRE option left ...<br>
<br>
Have your cleric ROOT the mob. And then you, the warrior gets CLOSER to it than the monk. And the monk makes sure he stays further away than you the duration of the fight. That'll stick aggro on your warrior pretty seamlessly.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scottsh>scottsh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boardpics.bravepages.com/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/13/03 12:09:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4821.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: nod</span><hr size=1> Wubao - those are definately the tactics we've used to keep the aggro on me (although not the rooting option - beating on the mob causes root to break very quickly in my experience, I'm not sure how good a tactic that would be.)<br>
